# App structure

## Purpose

Personal software documentation site. Markdown-only content, rendered for readers.

## Audience

- **Readers:** public visitors browsing documentation
- **Admins:** invited users who manage content (bootstrap creates the first admin)

## Auth model

- First registered user becomes **admin** (bootstrap)
- After bootstrap: **invite-only** — new admins must be invited at `/admin/users`
- Invitations emailed via Gmail SMTP (or copy-link fallback); acceptance at `/invite/[token]`
- Admin uses in-app editor to create, edit, and manage doc pages
- **Mandatory TOTP (authenticator app)** for every signed-in admin — public doc visitors are never prompted
- Enrollment at `/admin/security/2fa` after first sign-in; sign-in challenge at `/login/two-factor`
- 2FA cannot be disabled once enabled

## Content

- Storage format: **Markdown only** in Postgres (`document` table)
- Public site reads published documents from DB
- Style: software documentation (guides, reference, API docs)

## v1 primary action

Admin signs in and manages documentation via CodeMirror editor at `/admin/documents/*`.

## Folder conventions

- `src/lib/components/admin/` — admin shell and editor
- `src/lib/components/docs/` — public docs layout
- `src/lib/schemas/` — Zod validation schemas
- `src/lib/server/services/` — docs, settings, categories
